Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) performs a convolution operation on an image using filters (kernels).
The calculation’s main purpose is:

Purpose of This Calculation

The CNN uses these calculations to detect important features from an image, such as:

Edges
Shapes
Textures
Patterns
Object parts

This is how CNN “understands” images before classification.

What Happens in This Image?

The image has 3 channels:

Red Channel
Green Channel
Blue Channel (RGB)

Each channel has:

Input pixel values
A small filter/kernel (3×3 matrix)

The CNN performs:

Multiply input values with kernel values
Add all results
Add bias
Produce one output value
Example from the Image

For Red Channel:

Input values × Kernel values
→ Result = 314

For Green Channel:

→ Result = −175

For Blue Channel:

→ Result = 326

Then CNN combines all channels:

314+(−175)+326+Bias(1)

Final Output:

466

The value 466 becomes one pixel in the output feature map.

Why Is This Useful?

This calculation helps CNN identify patterns.

Example:

| Filter Learns  | Detects                |
| -------------- | ---------------------- |
| Edge filter    | Borders of objects     |
| Texture filter | Fabric patterns        |
| Shape filter   | Eyes, wheels, shirts   |
| Color filter   | Specific color regions |


